    narrator "{i}Avyanna considers.{/i}"
    narrator "{i}The mine taught her that power doesn't ask permission. The Garden taught her that sustainable systems do.{/i}"
    narrator "{i}But the mine also taught her that some people only understand force. And the Garden showed her that even the Sutured Houses have safety signs-boundaries enforced, not just suggested.{/i}"
    avyanna "{i}[[slowly]]{/i} They violated consent first. They tried to take me without asking. So... the locality rules changed?"
